==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fascet
<hw>Fas"cet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Glass Making)</fld>
<def>A wire basket on the end of a rod to carry glass bottles, etc., to
the annealing furnace; also, an iron rod to be thrust into the mouths of
bottles, and used for the same purpose; -- called also
<altname>pontee</altname> and <altname>punty</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fascia</ent>⟦br⟧
